  "texts": [
    "4) Update the perturbation based on the objective type:gradient ascent for PCA+ (obj = +) to induce diffusion collapse, or gradient descent for PCA-(obj = -) to induce concentration collapse (Lines 8-13).",
    "5) Project the perturbation into the ℓ ∞ ball to satisfy the imperceptibility constraint (Line 15).",
    "6) Update the adversarial image while ensuring pixel values remain valid (Line 17).",
    "For PCA+, we set v = 1 to align with the standard normal prior used in VAE training, causing the posterior to diverge and create an out-of-distribution scenario.",
    "For PCA-, we set v = 1×10 -8 to approximate zero variance, forcing the posterior to collapse to a degenerate point mass."
